ATEEZ, short for ‚ÄòA TEEnager Z‚Äô, is an eight-member South Korean group that has taken the world by storm immediately after their debut in October 2018. Known for standout performances, the octet have turned storytelling into a full musical experience. The eight members of ATEEZ are HONGJOONG, SEONGHWA, YUNHO, YEOSANG, SAN, MINGI, WOOYOUNG, and JONGHO. Their group name stood for ‚Äòeverything teenagers need from A to Z‚Äô, and has since evolved alongside their fans (named ATINY) to become ‚Äòeverything you need from A to Z‚Äô. Establishing themselves as top artists early on in their career with a sold out global tour only four months after their debut, they continue to break their own records. In 2024, they dominated on the global stage, taking over festivals around the world with performances at Coachella (US) and Summer Sonic (JPN), even set to headline at Mawazine (MAR). With a unique narrative that starts from the very first release in the ‚ÄòTREASURE‚Äô album series and continues through the ‚ÄòFEVER‚Äô and ‚ÄòTHE WORLD‚Äô masterpieces, taking a turn into a new universe with the start of the ‚ÄòGOLDEN HOUR‚Äô series, the group combines bestseller narratives with personalized music that speaks to their generation. The pirates of the high K-pop seas ATEEZ have made their mark as a million seller group, topping the Billboard 200 with multiple releases.

snippet.title: We're Back to Cabin Life!
snippet.description:
After nearly 7 months away, we're finally back at our cabin in the woods! Thanks to AG1 for sponsoring this video. Head to https://drinkag1.com/eamonandbec for a special offer üíú 

Subscribe to our podcast! Weekly episodes coming soon:
https://youtube.com/@REROOTwithEamonandBec?si=if-TsNUT6o5Gbstk


Make sure you also check out our friends @RayaandLouis  They make amazing travel content with their little family. Their episode from their time with us at the cabin is now live here: 

We moved out to our cabin in the woods 4 years ago & every time summer comes around we forget just how much work it is to open the cabin for the "season" after our harsh Canadian winter. So, we get to work installing water lines, tidying the grounds and rescuing our floating docks. Craziest part is that we have a 7 month old joining us this time making us much, MUCH less productive üòú  Would you live at our cabin in the Canadian winter? Summer? or year round?

We're Eamon & Bec ((and Oso) and now Frankie!!). We once lived very minimally out of vans #vanlife but happily moved into the woods during the pandemic #cabinlife . When we found out we were going to have a baby we decided to also rent an apartment in the city so we can be surrounded by support and love!
